# public/circuitjs/ — vendored CircuitJS (gitignored)

This directory is intentionally gitignored. The vendored CircuitJS bundle
(~11 MB of GWT-compiled JavaScript + fonts) is fetched on demand and is
not tracked in git.

To populate this directory, run from the repo root:

    bash scripts/vendor-circuitjs.sh

To refetch from scratch:

    bash scripts/vendor-circuitjs.sh --force

CircuitJS is GPLv2 (Paul Falstad et al.). The vendor script also fetches
LICENSE.txt and writes NOTICE.txt alongside the bundle. Those two text
files ARE committed to git (force-added) so the license travels with the
project even when the binary blobs do not.

See README.md ("CircuitJS (vendored)") and
.project-memory/decisions/vendor-circuitjs-locally.md for context.
